label chapter6:

    # [Scene: North Beach Ridge | Night — The Storm]

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_1 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Low, relentless percussion — a storm's heartbeat]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Wind howling; coarse sand grinding underfoot; the intermittent cracking of driftwood]
    "You are wet through to your underlayers. The salt tastes metallic on your lips; your hair clings in a cold, stinging veil around your face. In your jacket pocket your notebook presses against your ribs like a small, steady thought — plan, promise, memory. Each breath fogs and disappears."
    "Volunteers move in ragged lines along the berm, shovels and arms wrapped in plastic against the wind. Sandbags clang against each other; ropes strain with each incoming wedge of sea. The community-built defenses sag at the"
    "joints where old canvas meets new patched tarps. You can feel the seams in your chest: every stitch was sewn by someone you know."
    "'Ivo!' you shout. Your voice is a thin thread over the roar. He is half-bent at the edge, rope in both hands, the glow from his cap lamp throwing short halos on the wet sand. He"
    "looks up, face cut by rain and exhaustion, and for a second there is a private softness — an answering arc — before the tide rips it back."
    show ivo_calder at left:
        zoom 0.7

    ivo_calder "They're hitting harder than the forecasts. We hold this ridge another five minutes, then shift volunteers to the southern bastion. Ronan—' (he jerks his chin toward a lit shape) '—can't lift those last bags alone."
    show ronan_pike at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ronan_pike "I'm on it. Give me two."
    "You move beside Ivo and the two of you loop a new anchor line into a hacked cleat. The rope bites into your palms; a smear of salt and sand leaves a gritty print on your"
    "skin. You smell diesel from the generator, old coffee in a thermos someone forgot. Somewhere behind, Oba's cane taps a steady tempo — an old rhythm against chaos."
    show oba_kofi at center:
        zoom 0.7

    oba_kofi "Call the line! Thicker knots! Lay the weight farther down the slope!"
    "You do. You instruct. You run. Leadership feels like chanting incantations into the wind, instructions given to keep bodies moving, to keep hope practical. But a new swell comes, taller than the rest. It crashes across the berm with a sound like a falling wall."
    hide ivo_calder
    hide ronan_pike
    hide oba_kofi

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_2 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A sickening rip, volunteer cries, the thwump of collapsing earth]
    "Your chest goes cold in a way the rain cannot touch. For one suspended moment you watch water take what you thought would hold. It pours through a breach — greedy, unstoppable — and downslope, a clutch of the lower houses stands in its path."
    "Ivo Calder grabs your arm. His fingers are raw, nails rimmed with sand. He doesn't speak at first; his jaw works, the most human thing in the storm. Then, with a rough, breathless humor he has"
    "used to buoy others, he says, 'Get Maya off Crane Lane. If we lose Crane, the pumps drown first.'"
    show alys_maren at left:
        zoom 0.7

    alys_maren "Ronan — you and Leyna take the eastern line. Oba, with me. Ivo, shore support."
    show ivo_calder at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ivo_calder "Cover the rowhouses. If we have to choose tonight, we choose people."
    "He moves like a machine wound with grief and resolve. You follow. Every instruction you give is an attempt to translate science and care into hands and rope."

    menu:
        "Shout faster, force the pace":
            "You bark orders, your voice scattering into the night. Volunteers snap into quicker movements; the eastern line gains decisive inches but your throat burns dry."
        "Move deliberately, double-check knots":
            "You slow and check each knot with your gloves numb. It costs time; two bags slip farther out, but the ones tied down hold better under the final swell."

    # --- merge ---
    "Whether the immediate rhythm is rushed or measured, you feel the price: some houses hold, some do not. The tide is a merciless arbiter."
    # [Scene Transition: Time Lapse — Storm through Night into Grey Dawn]
    hide alys_maren
    hide ivo_calder

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_3 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A diminished, aching string motif]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Dripping roofs; a chorus of low, tired voices]
    # [Scene: Harbor | Dawn — Aftermath]

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_4 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The distant weeping of a child; the scrape of a crowbar; muted sobbing]
    "Dawn reveals a town working in small, exhausted circles. Salt clings to your eyelashes. The smell here is cleaner — bruised kelp and the metallic tang of broken infrastructure. You walk along rows of houses, counting"
    "which ones still sit proud and which are half-submerged in a shallow, salt-slick pool. Volunteers trudge between them carrying jerrycans and stacks of tarp. You recognize a porch swing missing, a child's bike wedged in a"
    "doorway. You keep thinking of Oba's face when the tide took his net — that look of survival folded with memory."
    "Maya appears near the quay, apron muddy, hair braided with bits of seaweed. Her eyes are red but not empty. She moves like someone balancing grief and an urgent need to be useful."
    show maya_maren at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_maren "They're going to need a place. The Thomases—no, they can't stay in that lean-to. We have the hall but water—"
    show alys_maren at right:
        zoom 0.7

    alys_maren "We set the school up as temporary shelters. Ivo's crew can run the generator schedule. Ronan and the younger ones can handle food distribution."
    "Ivo Calder appears at your shoulder, workshirt shredded at the cuff, eyes rimmed with fatigue. The sharpness that used to nestle in his humor is now edged with a new, brittle clarity."
    show ivo_calder at center:
        zoom 0.7

    ivo_calder "We're strapped for supplies. The last pallet of tarps was used on Crane. Celine's emergency trucks are tied up elsewhere. If more homes go, people will be forced to move inland."

    alys_maren "People move — or people die. We needed more time, and we did what we could."

    ivo_calder "Alys. We did what we'd always done — the volunteers, the hands. But there are limits. You and your plans — they're for years. People need the next week."
    "The exchange should be softer, but it is not. Both your tones are raw from exertion; both are threaded with accusation that neither has the breath to soften."

    alys_maren "This isn't a competition. You know that."

    ivo_calder "I know. I just— I can't watch people lose their last good season because we insisted on patience."
    "Ronan returns with a creaky cart. He drops a crate by your feet and looks between you and Ivo like a hinge in a door no one wants to pass through."
    hide maya_maren
    show ronan_pike at left:
        zoom 0.7

    ronan_pike "We saved the school, saved the pumps in the north. Lost three boats, a greenhouse. Mrs. Alvarez is packing to go to her sister in Trenton."
    "Maya's face goes brittle; Oba stands a pace off, hands on his cane, eyes far away and unreadable."
    hide alys_maren
    show oba_kofi at right:
        zoom 0.7

    oba_kofi "The sea takes. It also tells. It will be the council of what we must do next."
    "There is a pressure behind Oba's words that you can't define — pride, warning, and a sorrow folded together. His look at you is complex: not blame, not absolution, only the weight of someone who has seen cycles repeat."

    menu:
        "Move straight into triage, put distance between you and Ivo":
            "You turn to marshal volunteers. The immediate work steadies you; you feel the distance with Ivo as a physical chill at your back."
        "Sit with Ivo and say nothing, wait to see if the heat passes":
            "You stay. Silence sits between you like an invisible raft. For a breath, the two of you merely watch the harbor; the unsaid words press like wet cloth against your chest."

    # --- merge ---
    "You choose. The harbor hums on."
    # [Scene: Muri Research Lab | Midday — The Tally]
    hide ivo_calder
    hide ronan_pike
    hide oba_kofi

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_5 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Sparse piano, each note a lonely bell]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The low hum of pumps; the static of a handheld radio; footsteps on metal grates]
    "Inside the lab, Leyna's tablet scrolls through the damage assessment: percent mortality in seagrass beds, the turbidity spike, the loss of one pilot installation. The fluorescents in the lab make the green of the seedlings seem fragile, unreal — a last, trembling promise."
    show dr_leyna_ortiz at left:
        zoom 0.7

    dr_leyna_ortiz "The turbidity surged during the peak. We lost a third of the transplant density in the north shoals. Recovery in that zone will require months of replanting and clean water windows we may not get if the season continues this way."
    "You move your hand over the graph, not reading numbers but tracing the shape of loss. Each dip feels like a bruise. Your notebook is open, pages damp at the edges. You write and then scratch out: 'replant schedule — volunteers' availability — emergency grant?'"
    "Ivo Calder stands near the doorway, arms folded. His jaw is set; the leather on his hands is caked with salt. He watches Leyna with an engineer's appraisal and a rescuer's impatience."
    show ivo_calder at right:
        zoom 0.7

    ivo_calder "We need to prioritize. Shoreline repairs that protect pumps and wells first. If we can't get the pumps, it doesn't matter how many seedlings we set."
    show alys_maren at center:
        zoom 0.7

    alys_maren "If we only focus on pumps and walls, we lock in the wrong future. We lose habitat that would make these structures last. The living solution has to be part of the protection."

    ivo_calder "And if we lose people to the sea while we wait for habitat to regrow?"
    "A beat. Leyna looks at both of you, listening to two languages: immediate risk and structural resilience."

    dr_leyna_ortiz "Both are right. Both are necessary. But resources are finite. The town will need to make choices about allocation. We can stretch volunteer hours. We cannot conjure material out of thin air."
    "You feel the town fold in on itself — a map of priorities sharpened into arrows pointing opposite ways."
    "Maya comes into the lab carrying a bundle. She sets it down with steady hands and looks at you both."
    hide dr_leyna_ortiz
    show maya_maren at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_maren "The Thomases left this morning. They took the last trailer. Oba says we'll ask the council for relocation assistance. People are packing the hall."
    "You look at Ivo. He looks at you. The conversation that should have space for patience has none; exhaustion has hollowed the margins."

    ivo_calder "Alys, I— I can't ask my crew to keep doing this without clearer protections. I can lead the rebuild south, set up modular shelters. I can—and I will—organize evacuations if you want the restoration. But I can't be both the person fixing roofs tonight and the person pushing for a ten-year seagrass plan who's not here when someone needs a ladder."
    "Your chest tightens. You remember the first evenings in the greenhouse when your hands trembled with fear, and his hands steadied your method. You remember laughter smeared over seed trays and a thousand small shared plans. Now words feel like currency neither of you can spend."

    alys_maren "So what do you want, Ivo?"

    ivo_calder "I want people to be safe. I want you to have your plan. I want us both to survive the next season. But I see things differently now. I think—maybe—some work needs to be done by teams that aren't built around a long waiting game. People need things they can touch and feel done."

    alys_maren "And us?"

    ivo_calder "Us—' (he runs a hand through his hair) '—I don't know. Maybe us is changing. Maybe being allies means sometimes walking parallel and not holding hands."
    "The words arrive like a tide; they do not sweep everything away but they change the shape of the shore. You look at him, and for a second you want to be angry, to tell him"
    "that compromise is betrayal. Instead, you find yourself listing the costs of telling the truth: losing people to storms, losing the thing you loved most about Saltwick."
    "Oba enters without ceremony. He has seen worse seasons. He stands and listens to the frayed exchange like one who measures seasons by their leaves."
    hide ivo_calder
    show oba_kofi at right:
        zoom 0.7

    oba_kofi "You both give in the ways you know. That is how you care. The sea will not choose your pain for you. You choose it."
    "Those words are not counsel; they're a counsel's sorrow. You accept them as such."

    menu:
        "Promise to step back from Ivo's crew, focus on restoration":
            "You agree, voice steady with the weight of decision. Ivo nods slowly, relief flashing across his face. The lab dims around you — a new, solitary path laid in the open."
        "Insist you will not abandon community-first protections — ask Ivo to stay":
            "You plead, hands trembling. Ivo's face collapses for a heartbeat into a childlike need. He opens his mouth and then closes it; the lab air fills with the quiet of something fraying beyond repair."

    # --- merge ---
    "You don't perform grand speeches. You make the choice that hurts less on paper but cuts deeper in the chest. Whether you stepped back or asked him to stay, the outcome lays down the grain of"
    "the next months: some will stay; some will go; the town will be smaller in familiar ways and larger in ways that matter less to you."
    # [Scene: Harbor Edge | Late Afternoon]
    hide alys_maren
    hide maya_maren
    hide oba_kofi

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_6 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A single, low cello note that holds]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Door slams, muffled goodbyes, the distant bark of a dog]
    "You walk with Maya toward the quay. She carries a folded blanket, her shoulders squared in a way that makes her fragile. A family of three secures a child's stuffed animal into a box. Mr. Alvarez,"
    "who spent his life mending nets, opens his palms and says nothing; the gesture carries both a resignation and a benediction."
    show maya_maren at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_maren "They offered rent assistance in Trenton. Oba says some elders will stay, watch the graves and the harvest. Not everyone can go."
    show alys_maren at right:
        zoom 0.7

    alys_maren "We'll keep the nursery alive. We'll reroute volunteers to critical pumps. Leyna and I will write emergency grants. The science still matters."

    maya_maren "It matters to you. It matters enough to keep you here."
    "You feel the compass beneath your jacket, a small weight of a life. Its brass ring is cold against your hand when you touch it. It doesn't tell you the right thing; it only sits the way a memory does."
    "Ivo Calder comes up beside you — not close enough for the old intimacy but present — and for a long heartbeat you both watch a convoy of cars leave in a thin line across the road. He doesn't reach for your hand."
    show ivo_calder at center:
        zoom 0.7

    ivo_calder "I'll head south with a few rigs. We'll set modular roofs at the camps, get water lines running. If the council approves, we'll have formal shelters within a week."

    alys_maren "You'll go?"

    ivo_calder "Someone has to be the person people can find when their floor caves. You know I can't sleep unless the smoke alarms work."
    "You both stand on the edge of the harbor and for once there is nothing like the sea to cut the conversation for you. The wind takes your sentence away as if to spare you both."

    ivo_calder "I love you, Alys. I always will. But love doesn't mean we walk the same path forever."
    "You inhale. The sentence settles in like salt in an old wound: necessary, inevitable, and stinging."

    alys_maren "Then go. Do the work the town needs. Keep people whole."
    "Ivo Calder nods, eyes raw. He doesn't say the words you both once dreamed — not here. He straightens his cap and walks toward the small convoy, shoulders squared to the task."
    "You watch him go until the damp outline of his back is a moving smudge. Then you return to the lab, to the seedlings and charts and the slow patient arithmetic of restoration."
    # [Scene: Muri Research Lab | Evening — Closure]
    hide maya_maren
    hide alys_maren
    hide ivo_calder

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_7 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A hesitant, minor-key lull — sorrow with a sharpened clarity]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A distant bell; the lab door shutting; the rustle of paper]

    "You sit at the bench and open your notebook. You write" "Repair pumps / Replant north shoals / Support relocations / Community oversight fund."
    "Maya leans against the bench and slides a steaming mug towards you. Her hand rests briefly over yours — a small, familial anchoring."
    show maya_maren at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_maren "You did everything you could tonight. We saved more than we lost."
    show alys_maren at right:
        zoom 0.7

    alys_maren "We saved who we could. Some left. Some stayed. And Ivo—"

    maya_maren "You'll both find where you belong. Maybe not together. Maybe beside each other in different ways. That doesn't make it less true."
    "You rest your forehead against the cool brass of the compass you cling to. It feels like a relic and a tool. Outside, the horizon bleeds a thin, stubborn strip of gold that is not promise but patience."
    "Oba Kofi enters and stands a moment near the doorway, watchful and unreadable. He lifts his cane in a small, solemn salute to the seedlings."
    show oba_kofi at center:
        zoom 0.7

    oba_kofi "We will plant. We will build. We will mourn. That is our way. The town will wear its scars like maps."
    "You listen and the map on your chest rearranges into a different geography — less romantic, more real. The work ahead is long. People have been displaced; supplies are thin; the recovery will be punctuated by small, hard victories."
    "At night you walk up to the lab's small observation window and look at the dark watered green in the tanks. The seedlings are alive. You touch the glass like a benediction. You think of Ivo"
    "on the road with his rigs, of Maya holding down the hall, of Oba's complex face. Love remains in the architecture of your life, but in a different room."

    "You make a final note" "Stay. Guard this patch. Teach the next crews."
    hide maya_maren
    hide alys_maren
    hide oba_kofi

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_8 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: The cello pulls one final, soft, unresolved chord]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The distant, steady return of the harbor bell — something to mark time more than to comfort]
    "You exhale. The town will be smaller in some ways and more stubborn in others. People will leave and return, seeds will need replanting, and for now the nights will be shorter, hands will be colder."
    "Your relationship with Ivo is changed; there is a seam there that both of you will carry. It is not the end of affection — merely the necessary rearrangement of lives after the storm."
    "You stand, braid your hair back with fingers that smell of salt and soil, and step outside. The air is sharp and clear. The sky is neither forgiving nor kind; it simply is. You feel a"
    "quiet resolve settle — not the naive hope of a daybreak, but the steady, determined patience of someone who will return tomorrow to plant again."

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_9 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Fades into a single, solemn piano note]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The soft lap of waves, a town's low murmur]

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_10 at full_bg
    "THE END"
    # [GAME END]
    return
